title: What can I do if I can't make a phone call when my phone receives the 4G or 3G signal?
answer:
Your phone displays the network signal in the following priority: 4G > 3G > 2G. 

 [Your phone supports calls over 2G networks only. If you make a phone call over a 4G or 3G network, you phone will turn to receive the 2G signal. If the 2G signal is unavailable in your area, take your phone to a place where the 2G signal is available and try again.]()
